-- BBVA, CAM, Colonial, Telefonica, Repsol May Move: Iberian Equity Preview
-- Francesca Cinelli
-- 2010-07-16T06:26:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-16/bbva-cam-colonial-telefonica-repsol-may-move-iberian-equity-preview.html

          
          
             The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Spanish and Portuguese trading. Stock
symbols are in parentheses and share prices are from the
previous close.  
 Spain’s  IBEX 35  Index fell 1.2 percent to 10,160.2.
Portugal’s PSI-20 Index rose 0.1 percent to 7,266.64.  
 Spanish stocks:  
 Abertis Infraestructuras SA  (ABE SM): The company may sell
its 32 percent stake in Eutelsat Communications SA for as much
as 2 billion euros ($2.6 billion) if a planned buyout bid by CVC
Capital Partners Ltd., Criteria CaixaCorp SA and Actividades de
Construccion y Servicios SA takes place, Expansion reported. The
shares dropped 1.4 percent to 13.92 euros.  
 Banco Bilbao Vizcaya Argentaria  (BBVA SM): Spain’s second-
largest bank was upgraded to “buy” from “neutral” at Goldman
Sachs Group Inc. The shares fell 2.1 percent to 9.57 euros.  
 Banco Sabadell SA  (SAB SM): The process of examining the
bank’s offer to buy Banco Guipuzcoano SA (GUI SM) has started,
Spain’s market regulator said. Sabadell fell 0.4 percent to 4.14
euros. Guipuzcoano slipped 0.2 percent to 4.93 euros.  
 Caja de Ahorros del Mediterraneo  (CAM SM): The lender which
had agreed to merge with a group of savings bank said in a
regulatory filing that it opposes the role of the future chief
executive officer in the combined group. The shares lost 1
percent to 5.90 euros.  
 Iberia Lineas Aereas de Espana SA  (IBLA SM): Spain’s
biggest airline had its price estimate trimmed to 3.1 euros from
3.3 euros at Goldman Sachs. The shares lot 2.7 percent to 2.38
euros.  
 Inditex SA  (ITX SM): The owner of the Zara clothing chain
will have stores in 50 Chinese cities within two years, Cinco
Dias said, citing Chief Executive Officer Pablo Isla.  
 The company will be present in 30 Chinese cities within ten
months and will expand to 50 within 24 months, Isla said at a
conference in Bilbao, the newspaper reported. The shares
retreated 0.4 percent to 50.47 euros.  
 Inmobiliaria Colonial SA  (COL SM): The builder may be
active as Spain’s housing ministry publishes second-quarter
house price data. The shares rose 0.9 percent to 11.7 cents.  
 Repsol YPF SA  (REP SM): Spain’s largest oil company was
raised to “outperform” from “underperform” at Credit Suisse
Group AG. The shares lost 0.5 percent to 17.83 euros.  
 Telefonica SA  (TEF SM): The phone company’s 7.15 billion-
euro offer for Portugal Telecom SGPS SA’s stake in Brazil’s
largest wireless company expires. The shares fell 0.6 percent to
16.42 euros.  
 Portuguese stocks:  
 Galp Energia SGPS SA  (GALP PL): Portugal’s biggest oil
company is scheduled to release its second-quarter trading
update. The stock fell 0.8 percent to 12.60 euros.  
